PREAMBLE

GaiaThinker is an open-visibility educational platform
built to serve British Columbia students, educators,
and school districts. This license makes the source
code visible for trust, transparency, and academic
review — while protecting the intellectual property,
mission, and integrity of the platform.

This is not a permissive open source license.
Visibility does not equal permission to copy,
deploy, or redistribute.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SECTION 1: WHAT YOU MAY DO (Permitted Uses)

The following are explicitly permitted without
requiring written permission from Gaialink
Intelligence Systems Inc.:

1.1 VIEWING AND REVIEW
    You may view, read, and study the source code
    for personal learning, academic research, or
    institutional security and privacy review.

1.2 SCHOOL DISTRICT REVIEW
    School districts, educators, and IT administrators
    may review this codebase in full to verify safety,
    privacy compliance, and pedagogical integrity
    before deploying GaiaThinker in their schools.

1.3 ACADEMIC RESEARCH
    Researchers at accredited academic institutions
    may reference and cite this codebase in
    peer-reviewed research, with proper attribution
    to Gaialink Intelligence Systems Inc.

1.4 CONTRIBUTING
    You may submit pull requests, bug reports,
    and suggested improvements via GitHub.
    All accepted contributions become the property
    of Gaialink Intelligence Systems Inc. under
    this license, unless a separate contributor
    agreement is signed.

1.5 PERSONAL STUDY
    Individual developers may study this code
    to learn techniques and approaches, provided
    they do not reproduce substantial portions
    in their own commercial or public projects.

