SECTION 2: WHAT YOU MAY NOT DO (Prohibited Uses)

The following are strictly prohibited without
prior written permission from Gaialink
Intelligence Systems Inc.:

2.1 COMMERCIAL USE
    You may not use this software, in whole or
    in part, for any commercial purpose, including
    but not limited to: selling access, charging
    subscription fees, licensing to third parties,
    or incorporating into a commercial product.

2.2 REDISTRIBUTION
    You may not redistribute this software,
    in whole or in part, in source or compiled
    form, through any channel including but not
    limited to: GitHub forks made public,
    npm packages, app stores, or direct download
    sites.

2.3 DERIVATIVE WORKS
    You may not create derivative works based
    on this software without explicit written
    permission. This includes rebranded versions,
    translated versions, or modified versions
    deployed under a different name or brand.

2.4 REMOVAL OF COPYRIGHT
    You may not remove, alter, or obscure any
    copyright notices, license notices, or
    attribution statements contained in this
    software or its documentation.

2.5 COMPETITIVE USE
    You may not use this codebase, its architecture,
    its educational content, its AI prompt designs,
    or its pedagogical framework to build a
    competing educational product without prior
    written agreement with Gaialink Intelligence
    Systems Inc.

2.6 AI TRAINING
    You may not use this source code, educational
    content, AI prompts, or scenario data as
    training data for any artificial intelligence
    or machine learning model without explicit
    written permission.

2.7 IMPERSONATION
    You may not deploy any version of this software
    in a way that implies endorsement by, or
    affiliation with, Gaialink Intelligence Systems
    Inc., the New Westminster School District,
    or any Indigenous Nations or communities
    referenced in the platform.

