SECTION 3: EDUCATIONAL CONTENT

3.1 The educational content contained in this
    platform — including BC climate scenarios,
    Indigenous land stewardship descriptions,
    stakeholder voices, Socratic question frameworks,
    and the Professor Ember AI tutor design —
    is the original intellectual property of
    Gaialink Intelligence Systems Inc.

3.2 Indigenous knowledge, cultural practices,
    and community voices referenced in this
    platform are included with deep respect
    and are not available for reproduction,
    adaptation, or reuse without consultation
    with the relevant First Nations communities
    and written permission from
    Gaialink Intelligence Systems Inc.

3.3 All verified data cited in this platform
    is sourced from publicly available government
    and peer-reviewed sources, as documented
    in the README. The selection, framing,
    and pedagogical application of that data
    is the intellectual property of
    Gaialink Intelligence Systems Inc.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SECTION 4: SCHOOL DISTRICT AND PILOT PARTNERS

4.1 School districts approved for the GaiaThinker
    pilot program receive a separate written
    agreement that governs their specific
    deployment rights, data handling procedures,
    and feedback obligations.

4.2 Pilot participation does not grant any
    intellectual property rights beyond those
    explicitly stated in the pilot agreement.

4.3 Student data collected during approved pilots
    remains subject to BC FIPPA and PIPEDA,
    as described in the platform privacy policy.

